            <p>KLM Airlines is the oldest airline in the world based in the Netherlands, headquartered in Amstelveen. The airline serves 133 destinations in 70 countries on five continents from its hub at Amsterdam Airport Schiphol with a fleet size of 149 aircraft. KLM Airlines is known for its in-flight entertainment, catering, delft blue house, ground services, and bus services.  </p>
            <p>If you have plans to <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/klm-airlines.aspx">book flight tickets from KLM Airlines</a>, make sure you check the ongoing offers and deals to save on your traveling. Below is an overview of KLM Airlines’ cancellation policy for your ease. </p>
            <h2>Cancellation policy</h2>
            <p>According to <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/klm-airlines-cancellation-policy.aspx">KLM Airlines’ cancellation policy</a>, if you book a flight to/from the United States, and you cancel the flight ticket within 24 hours of booking, you are entitled to a full refund. If you fail to cancel your ticket within the cancellation window, you will have to pay the cancellation fees. Also, if you couldn’t board the flight due to the death or illness of a co-passenger, you can apply for a refund with relevant documents as proof. If the airline cancels or delays your flight, the airline will reschedule your flight. </p>
            <h3>Refund Policy</h3>
            <p>The airline doesn’t support <b>refund policy</b> regardless of any fare and class of service booked but they offer credits on your name for future travel that would be valid for a year from the date of issuance. Also, when the airline cancels or delays your flight, they will reschedule your flight and if the arrangements don’t suit your travel needs, you can claim a refund of the unused part of the ticket. </p>
            <h2>FAQs</h2>

            <h3>How to cancel a flight ticket with KLM Airlines? </h3>
            <p>If you wish to cancel the flight ticket, you may call the KLM Airlines customer care office and inform them about the cancellation. Also, you can visit the official website of the airlines and cancel your flight ticket. </p>
            <h3>How can I make the request for a refund? By when can I expect it? </h3>
            <p>In order to make a request for a refund, you can visit the official website of KLM Airlines or call customer care. It may take 7 to 10 business days for the refund to reflect on your card/bank statement. </p>
            <h3>Can I ask for compensation if my flight gets delayed by 2 hours? </h3>
            <p>There can be a possibility that your replacement flight delays your arrival by 2 or more hours or your flight was canceled less than 14 days before departure, you are eligible to get compensation. </p>
            <h3>Is my flight refundable? </h3>
            <p>Though such information is mentioned on the ticket, you can check if your flight is refundable by visiting the official website of the airline and entering the ticket or document number. It will display refund eligibility and information. </p>
